  "commentary": "**DEALER HEDGING COMMENTARY:**\n\nWith SPX at 6815 sitting right between the max negative gamma at 6810 (-58960M) and max positive gamma at 6830 (+14398M), dealers are caught in heavy short gamma territory and likely forced to buy this breakout move aggressively. The massive negative GEX wall cluster from 6800-6820 creates a dangerous amplification zone where dealer hedging will accelerate any directional move - they're buying rallies here, not providing resistance. Key level to watch is the 6830 max positive gamma strike where dealer behavior flips to selling pressure, while any pullback toward the 6810-6800 negative walls will trigger more dealer buying.\n\n**Bottom line:** expect violent moves in either direction with dealers adding fuel to the fire rather than providing stability.",
